FBIS4-60147 "drnes099_n_94012" FBIS-NES-94-099 Daily Report 22 May 1994 LEBANON Reaction to al-Dirani Seizure Reported Reaction to al-Dirani Seizure Reported Minister Urges Unity Against Israel NC2205165394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 22 May 94 NC2205165394 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] Commenting on the abduction of al-Hajj Mustafa al-Dirani, Housing and Cooperatives Minister Mahmud Abu Hamdan has condemned the Zionist act of piracy and urged unity against the Israeli crimes. He said the Israeli operation proves that no region in Lebanon is safe from the Israeli danger. He said the people must remain united to confront Israel and support resistance to serve the objectives of liberation. He said Israeli terrorism is nothing new and the latest operation in Qasr Naba proves that Israel is still the same and its talk of peace is a worthless illusion.
